parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the belt to malfunction, leading to a lack of proper restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract
the seat belt gets stuck
the seat belt will not lock into place
the motorized seat belt seizes
the shoulder belt does not secure the passenger
the passenger side automatic seat belt comes off the track
the seat belt will not move when opening or closing the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to honor the recall and repair the defective seat belt can lead to a lack of proper restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The manufacturer refuses to repair the defective seat belt
the dealer claims the vehicle is not included in the recall
the dealer refuses to honor the recall
the manufacturer does not provide reimbursement for previous repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down without warning, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down without warning
the vehicle hesitates or stalls when approaching a stop or making a turn
the vehicle has a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, and even fires, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
causing issues with the dashboard
speedometer
and oil gauge
the windshield wipers
radio
and other accessories turn on and off randomly
a fire starts under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire due to an electrical short
the fuse panel catches on fire
a fire starts at the headlight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down without warning, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition switch locks up
the vehicle stalls or shuts down without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seatbelt system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's side 3-point automatic seatbelt fails to move forward or backward on its track
despite the motor running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An ignition switch failure can cause the engine to continue running even after the key is removed, leading to overheating, fires, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine fails to shut off when the ignition switch is turned off and the key is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking coolant hoses can cause engine overheating, leading to damage and potential failure.
symptoms: Coolant hoses for the turbocharger leak in small quantities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage and lead to premature wear.
symptoms: The valve cover gasket leaks oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed timing belt can cause engine damage and lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The timing belt fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust fumes entering the vehicle can cause health problems and discomfort for occupants.

causing burning sensations in the eyes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unusual engine noises can indicate underlying problems that may lead to engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective rocker arm gaskets can cause oil leaks and engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed pulley can cause engine damage and lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The pulley fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system problems can cause health issues and discomfort for occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked radiator can cause engine overheating, leading to damage and potential failure.
